1
00:00:04,249 --> 00:00:10,801
You have your duty to perform 
and don’t be attached to the result,

2
00:00:10,801 --> 00:00:17,655
don’t expect to enjoy
the fruits of that work:

3
00:00:17,815 --> 00:00:23,365
mā phala, mā phaleṣu kadācana— 
the fruits are not meant for you.

4
00:00:23,605 --> 00:00:26,765
[The Art of Work | Karma]

5
00:00:27,506 --> 00:00:36,486
So, and then He’s cautiously saying,
“This precludes … [Hare Kṛṣṇa]

6
00:00:36,496 --> 00:00:45,336
That if you’re calculating 
about this, and you think,

7
00:00:46,516 --> 00:00:53,516
“Why should I work, if I’m not going 
to enjoy the fruit of that work?

8
00:00:53,538 --> 00:01:02,018
So, I’ll go on strike.”
Śrīla Guru Mahārāj reminds us that,

9
00:01:02,028 --> 00:01:11,908
“No, you are to do your duty,
and the result is for Kṛṣṇa.”

10
00:01:12,815 --> 00:01:21,115
And we have to learn
this type of working attitude.

11
00:01:21,115 --> 00:01:24,426
In another place in the Gītā 
it’s called

12
00:01:24,426 --> 00:01:27,426
yogaḥ karmasu kauśalam,

13
00:01:27,426 --> 00:01:31,170
which you could render as
‘the art of work’.

14
00:01:31,170 --> 00:01:34,640
What is the art of working?

15
00:01:35,250 --> 00:01:39,250
We hear also the maxim 
‘a labour of love’,

16
00:01:39,250 --> 00:01:42,250
means that there are maybe 
some labour involved,

17
00:01:42,250 --> 00:01:48,080
some inconvenience, 
some demands of your time, energy,

18
00:01:48,080 --> 00:01:53,400
but if it is for someone
for whom you have affection,

19
00:01:53,400 --> 00:01:55,870
for whom you have 
love and affection,

20
00:01:55,870 --> 00:02:01,770
then gladly, happily
we’ll accept that.

21
00:02:01,899 --> 00:02:07,969
Bhakti Vinod Ṭhākur has written
in one of his songs that

22
00:02:07,969 --> 00:02:13,923
whatever inconvenience 
or trouble comes to me

23
00:02:13,923 --> 00:02:19,453
that’s related to sevā— 
that’s a source of joy.

24
00:02:20,513 --> 00:02:29,053
I told the other day the example
about the mother in labour.

25
00:02:29,819 --> 00:02:41,529
So, this intense pain comes, 
especially in those final hours.

26
00:02:41,939 --> 00:02:47,749
It’s getting more and more intense 
until at last the baby is born,

27
00:02:47,749 --> 00:02:51,779
and then 
there is a source of joy.

28
00:02:51,990 --> 00:02:56,402
We have to have this
in the background

29
00:02:56,402 --> 00:03:02,162
of how and why we move,
what it is we do.

